# topics.dcf — the controlled topic vocabulary for foundations and knowledge concepts.
#
# ONE topic per foundation module (meta.dcf `Topic:`) and per knowledge concept
# page (frontmatter `topic:`). RECORD ORDER IN THIS FILE = DISPLAY ORDER everywhere
# topics are grouped (sidebar sections, README index tables) — order the records
# curriculum-logically, early material first.
#
# Format: read.dcf records separated by blank lines. Fields:
#   Slug:        kebab-case id used in meta.dcf / frontmatter (stable once assigned)
#   DisplayName: human label for sidebar sections and index tables
# NOTE for loaders: base R's read.dcf has NO comment support — strip `^#` lines
# first: read.dcf(textConnection(grep("^#", readLines(f), value=TRUE, invert=TRUE)))
#
# Add/rename topics here, never inline in a module. Renaming a Slug means updating
# every module/page that carries it (grep first). Keep the list small (~6-10) — a
# topic with one module in it forever is a concept, not a topic.
#
# Grouping/enforcement is live: gen-indexes.R and gen-kb-index.R group by topic
# and fail --check for topics not listed here.
#
# This vocabulary ships as an EXAMPLE (like learner-profile.md) — forkers replace
# the records with their own domain's areas; keep the format.

Slug: arithmetic-and-algebra
DisplayName: Arithmetic & algebra

Slug: calculus
DisplayName: Calculus

Slug: linear-algebra
DisplayName: Linear algebra

Slug: probability
DisplayName: Probability

Slug: statistical-inference
DisplayName: Statistical inference

Slug: regression-and-models
DisplayName: Regression & models

Slug: computing-and-r
DisplayName: Computing & R
